<plot>Sir Michael REDGRAVE &amp; Joan GREENWOOD narrate a social history of Victorian Britain as reflected in the Music Hall songs of the time performed by James BOOTH, Eira HEATH, David KERNAN, Patsy ROWLANDS &amp; Sir Michael REDGRAVE. Much of the program is stills from the song sheets of the time &amp; animation based on contemporary prints cut with brief shots of narration to camera &amp; songs sung in a Music Hall setting.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?514854</url></doc>
